(firstQuint)Comparing Effectiveness of the Hydrus Microstent (TM) to Two iStents to Lower IOP in Phakic Eyes.

 This is a prospective, multicenter, single-masked, randomized clinical trial comparing the Hydrus Microstent to two iStent implants for the reduction of intraocular pressure in phakic patients with a positive diagnosis of primary open angle glaucoma, pseudoexfoliative glaucoma, or pigmentary dispersion glaucoma.

 Post-operative follow-up visits will be conducted at regular intervals.

